<br>
It's disgusting to me that a company would do this, make communication a one way street.<br>
<br>
If they would respond to the ingame /feedback issues then possibly they would have had less complaints on their board.  Where else does one go when they have an issue?  Have you tried calling their 800 number?  I have, its futile.  Go to the chat room (which deletes your petition btw) and try to have your question answered by 1 GM in the chat room while 200 other people are trying to get his attention?<br>
<br>
There are too many times when Verant has stated an issue is not an issue and then had to eat their words because of the posters in gameplay.<br>
<br>
-Alchemy<br>
-Racial Trade Skills<br>
-PvP Xteaming<br>
-Deleveling<br>
-Underused Zones<br>
-Items overpowered/underpowered<br>
<br>
I really think that the boards helped VI, if they had not just instantly discounted everyone who posted there as a whiner and a baby and moderated the forum correctly.  Instead, they responded to the poor posts and ignored the well documented posts that proved VI was wrong, but VI never admits they are wrong, even when they correct it.<br>
<br>
Poster posts a problem<br>
VI says no problem<br>
Poster reposts problem and others chime in<br>
VI says no problem<br>
Continue for 2 months<br>
Patch goes in correcting problem, credit given to in-house testers (&quot;we at VI found that by pressing combine with the proper ingredients, you actually cannot make the +5 helm of Cat-Ass, it has been fixed.&quot;....&quot;We at VI have found that indeed, the Belt of Womanly Essence isn't in the game, therefore we have upped the drop rate on them&quot;.)<br>
<br>
I was right on the heal/aggro changes and I think anyone who knew the high level game could tell you the way they did it, it wouldn't work.  It didn't work and VI had to eat another patch to fix it.  They didn't even test it on the Test server for god's sake.<br>
<br>
Yes, Rome is burning.<br>
<br>
Herder, who seriously thinks its time to cancel.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>5</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/29/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:18:29 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Whineplay sucked.  For every thoughtful post, there were around 500 thoughtless, ignorant posts.<br>
<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#212141><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uherdervazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HerderVazaelle</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>51</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/29/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:30:15 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: ...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">So, instead of punishing the flamers and trollers, rewarding the well thought out posts with a &quot;You know, you may be right, I will check it&quot; post that would take a few seconds, you should just delete the whole thing?<br>
