<br>
This is Verants fault, not the players.<br>
<br>
Herder.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ufaddlefiddlethebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faddle Fiddle the Bard</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>49</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3/29/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1:13:23 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Food</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have to agree with Herder.<br>
<br>
There were some real legitimate threads that came about on the whineplay boards.  Yeah you had to do some sifting, but it was generally fairly easy to pick out which ones where just stupid attention getters and which ones were good reading/commenting.<br>
<br>
A gent posting &quot;Here's a good reason why wizards should get Mez!&quot; is a candidate for the trash..and of course there were the regulars that you KNEW couldn't post anything you'd want to read...though they might have been fairly entertaining.<br>
<br>
